Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Lightly grease a baking sheet. Pour soda and buttermilk into a large bowl. Stir in baking mixing until dough pulls together. Knead dough in bowl until smooth. Flatten dough and cut into 6 rounds. Place biscuits on pan and brush with melted butter. Bake in preheated oven until golden brown, about 18 to 20 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes before serving.